  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rapid Response Window:
At least two thirds of CERF allocations are intended for disbursement through its Rapid Response window (RR). Allocations from this window promote early response to humanitarian needs by funding critical, life-saving humanitarian activities in the initial stages of a new humanitarian crises or in the case of a significant deterioration of an existing emergency.

Underfunded Emergencies Window:
Up to one third of CERF&apos;s allocations are intended for underfunded emergencies through its Underfunded Emergencies window (UFE). These allocations are made in two rounds during the year, and they allow partners to carry out life-saving activities in places where humanitarian responses are severely underfunded.</narrative>
  </description>
